# Accessibility Standards

## Semantic HTML
- Use appropriate HTML elements for their intended purpose
- Implement proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)
- Apply ARIA attributes only when native HTML semantics are insufficient
- Use landmark regions (main, nav, footer, etc.) appropriately

## Keyboard Navigation
- Ensure all interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Implement logical tab order for form elements
- Create appropriate focus styles for interactive elements
- Use focus trapping for modal interfaces

## Screen Reader Support
- Provide alternative text for images and icons
- Implement proper form labels for all inputs
- Use aria-live regions for dynamic content updates
- Test with screen readers during development

## Color and Contrast
- Maintain minimum contrast ratios (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
- Never use color alone to convey information
- Implement high contrast mode support
- Test color blindness scenarios

## Testing Requirements
- Include accessibility tests in component test suites
- Use automated testing tools (jest-axe, Lighthouse)
- Conduct manual keyboard navigation testing
- Document accessibility considerations for complex components

